# Offer of Internship — AI Intern

Date: «[Date of Offer]»

Dear [Candidate Name],

We are pleased to offer you a fixed‑term internship with Omninuera for the position of AI Intern. This letter summarizes the principal terms of the internship. Please review the terms carefully. This offer is a draft intended for legal review; do not implement legal changes without Legal's input.

1. Position and Reporting
   - Role/Title: AI Intern.
   - Reporting Manager: [Reporting Manager].
   - Location: This role is completely remote. The internship is governed by the employment jurisdiction of Bengaluru, India (see Governing Law clause below).

2. Term and Start Date
   - Duration: Fixed‑term internship for a period of 3 months.
   - Start Date: [Start Date].
   - End Date: The internship will end three months after the Start Date unless extended in writing by mutual agreement.

3. Stipend and Payments
   - Stipend: INR 10,000 per month.
   - Payment Schedule: Stipend will be paid monthly in arrears, subject to standard payroll processing timelines and applicable deductions.
   - Taxes and Deductions: The stipend is subject to any applicable taxes, statutory deductions, or withholdings required by law. As this is an internship (stipend only), the candidate is not eligible for regular employee benefits unless expressly stated in writing.

4. Working Hours and Expectations
   - Typical Weekly Hours: The internship is expected to require approximately [Typical Weekly Hours — e.g., 20] hours per week. Final weekly hours and schedule will be agreed with the Reporting Manager.
   - Remote Working Arrangements: The role is fully remote. The intern is expected to have a reliable internet connection and an appropriate work environment.
   - Deliverables and Performance: The intern will work on projects and deliverables as assigned by the Reporting Manager. Regular check‑ins, status updates, and any required documentation should be provided as requested.

5. Benefits and Policies
   - Benefits: This internship provides a stipend only. The intern is not entitled to Omninuera's regular employee benefits (such as paid leave, health insurance, or retirement benefits) unless explicitly provided in writing.
   - Company Policies: The intern is required to comply with Omninuera's policies, including but not limited to codes of conduct, IT/security policies, and data protection policies.

6. Confidentiality and Intellectual Property
   - Confidentiality: The intern will be required to keep confidential all proprietary and confidential information of Omninuera, both during and after the internship. The intern must not disclose such information to any third party except as authorized in writing by Omninuera.
   - Assignment of Inventions and IP: The intern agrees that any work product, inventions, discoveries, designs, software, documentation, or other deliverables created or developed by the intern during the internship that relate to Omninuera's business or result from work performed for Omninuera (collectively, "Work Product") shall be the exclusive property of Omninuera. The intern hereby assigns (or will assign) all right, title, and interest in such Work Product to Omninuera and agrees to execute any documents necessary to effectuate such assignment.
   - Right to Use Work Product: Omninuera shall have the exclusive right to use, reproduce, modify, distribute, and otherwise exploit any Work Product created by the intern in connection with the internship.

7. Termination
   - Early Termination: Either party may terminate this internship relationship by providing seven (7) calendar days' prior written notice to the other party.
   - Immediate Termination for Cause: Omninuera may terminate the internship immediately for cause, including but not limited to breach of this agreement, violation of company policies, misconduct, negligence, or any act that materially harms Omninuera.
   - Effect of Termination: Upon termination, the intern will return all Company property and confidential materials and will cease using any Omninuera systems or accounts.

8. Background Checks and Compliance
   - This offer is conditional upon the successful completion of any background checks and reference checks as required by Omninuera.
   - The offer is also conditional on compliance with Omninuera's onboarding requirements and company policies.

9. Governing Law
   - This internship and this offer letter shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws applicable in Bengaluru, Karnataka, India. The parties submit to the exclusive/ non‑exclusive (HR to choose per company policy) jurisdiction of the courts located in Bengaluru for any disputes arising out of this offer.

10. Conditional on Legal Review
    - This draft offer is provided for review. The offer is conditional on legal review; do NOT implement legal changes without direction from Legal. Legal may provide suggested changes which should be applied by HR only after review and approval.

11. Acceptance
    - To accept this offer, please sign and date below and return a scanned/photographed copy to HR by email. This offer will remain open until [Offer Expiry Date — optional] unless earlier revoked.

Signatures

